55.7	Sonia_Gandhi	Sonia Gandhi	Sonia Gandhi (born Antonia Edvige Albina Maino on 9 December 1946) is an Italian-born Indian politician and the President of the Indian National Congress, one of the major political parties of India. She is the widow of former Prime Minister of India, Rajiv Gandhi and belongs to Nehruâ€“Gandhi family. After his assassination in 1991, she was invited by the Indian National Congress to take over the Congress but refused and publicly stayed away from politics amidst constant prodding by the Congress. She finally agreed to join politics in 1997; in 1998, she was elected as the leader of the Congress.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/89/Gandhisonia05052007.jpg/250px-Gandhisonia05052007.jpg
